Comparisons of Buses: Time, Status, Type.

Plot 1 - Comparing lateness of Frequent and Local buses.

Local buses seem to be more late than Frequent buses

For Plot 1, I decided to compare local and frequent buses and how often they are late. The bus type was a new addition, because I didnt specify it before. Shown in the plot, local buses always seems to be more late compared to the frequent buses, although not by a significant amount. But then again, it was only a sample of 20 total, 10 each for the bus type, so more data could produce a better conclusion.

Plot 2 - Comparing mean minutes of early and delayed

For Plot 2, I wanted to know if there was a difference when it came to how many minutes a bus is delayed or early by - if they were any different. It seems that delayed buses have a much higher variation than early buses, but the means are very close to each other. I think delayed buses have more variation because it happens more often than early, with factors like traffic.

Plot 3 - comparing on time and delayed buses with time logged

On time seems to happen more often compared to delayed

For Plot 3, I decided to see which status happened more during the time I Logged these observations. As shown on the graph, on time happens more often than delayed buses - during the time I logged them in anyway. This is only data from local and frequent buses, so the sample is small. I would guess the delayed mostly came from local buses. I logged most of this data when it was morning or afternoon.
